casebody.data:
John TEIXEIRA; Steve Nobriga; Gary Gamaza; Calguns Foundation, Inc., (CGF); Second Amendment Foundation, Inc., (SAF); California Association of Federal Firearms Licensees, (CAL-FFL), Plaintiffs-Appellants, v. COUNTY OF ALAMEDA; Alameda County Board of Supervisors, as a policy making body; Wilma Chan, in her official capacity; Nate Miley, in his official capacity; Keith Carson, in his official capacity, Defendants-Appellees. No. 13-17132 United States Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Filed December 27, 2016

D.C. No. 3:12-cv-03288-WHO

ORDER

THOMAS, Chief Judge:

Upon the vote of a majority of nonre-cused active judges, it is ordered that this case be reheard en banc pursuant to Fed*1047eral Rule of Appellate Procedure 35(a) and Circuit Rule 35-3. The three-judge panel opinion shall not be cited as precedent by or to any court of the Ninth Circuit.
